# TcGVL File Format

## Standard GVL

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<TcPlcObject Version="1.1.0.1" ProductVersion="3.1.4024.15">
  <GVL Name="GVL_Example" Id="{GUID}">
    <Declaration><![CDATA[
VAR_GLOBAL
    gbSystemReady : BOOL;
    gfActualSpeed : REAL;
END_VAR
]]></Declaration>
  </GVL>
</TcPlcObject>
```

## Constant GVL (Parameters)

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<TcPlcObject Version="1.1.0.1" ProductVersion="3.1.4024.15">
  <GVL Name="Param_Example" Id="{GUID}">
    <Declaration><![CDATA[
VAR_GLOBAL CONSTANT
    cMaxRetries : UINT := 3;
    cTimeout    : TIME := T#5S;
END_VAR
]]></Declaration>
  </GVL>
</TcPlcObject>
```

## Rules

- GVLs have **only** `<Declaration>`, no `<Implementation>` section
- Each GVL needs ONE unique GUID
- Naming: `GVL_[Domain]` for runtime globals, `Param_[Library]` for constants
- `Global_Version` GVL for library version info (uses `ST_LibVersion` from `Tc2_System`)
